# GitHub Personal Access Token for nornslist discovery (GraphQL classify + code
# search + repo search). Local use only — in GitHub Actions the workflow uses the
# auto-provided secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN, so this file is NOT used there.
#
# IMPORTANT — use a PUBLIC-ONLY token so the key cannot read private repos at all:
# 1. Visit https://github.com/settings/tokens
# 2. "Generate new token" -> "Generate new token (classic)"
# 3. Name it "norns-ingest" or similar
# 4. Scopes: select ONLY "public_repo". Do NOT grant "repo" — that scope includes
#    private access. (As a backstop, nornslist also drops any repo GitHub reports as
#    private before classifying it, but a public-only key means it can never see one.)
# 5. Generate, copy the token.
# 6. Save this file as "gh.api" (drop the .example) and replace the line below with
#    just the token (no quotes, no newlines).
#
# Without a token, discovery falls back to unauthenticated GitHub (60 req/hr) and
# code search is unavailable, so most scripts won't be found.
ghp_REPLACE_THIS_WITH_YOUR_TOKEN
